<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="241" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1374,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1590,1616]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilela &amp; Junior &amp; Furieri &amp; Lencioni" authorityYear="2021" box="[434,519,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeromei">
<emphasis box="[434,519,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">jeromei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(noun in the genitive case) after Jérôme Constant, Hemiptera expert, Direction Taxonomy and Phylogeny and collection management expert at the Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences (IRSNB), for his great contributions to the odonatology, mainly working with the Selys’ collection curation and for helping us many times over the years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="243" pageId="1" pageNumber="241" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1374,1977]" box="[199,478,1734,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,478,1734,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[375,478,1734,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1374,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis box="[199,267,1770,1796]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">Head.</emphasis>
Labrum, anteclypeus, postclypeus, antefrons and genae black; two brownish small D-shaped spots (on each side of lateral ocelli); a large transversal pale stripe ranging from the postocular lobes through the occipital area, slightly darker in the occipital area; remainder of the head matte black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1374,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[295,386,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,198,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[155,1433,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus: a—dorsal view of a lectotype of Leptagrion andromache Hagen in Selys, 1876 and paratype´s labels (IRSNB); b—lateral view of L. andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; c—lateral view of holotype of Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (FAAL); d—Comparison between Leptagrion andromache and Leptagrion jeromei forewing pterostigma." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704350/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">Figs. 1c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[398,469,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[269,1331,193,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[256,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male prothorax in lateral view: a—Leptagrion andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; b—Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (holotype—FAAL); male hind lobe of prothorax in dorsal view: c—Leptagrion andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; d—Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (holotype—FAAL)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704352/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">2b, 2c</figureCitation>
). Prothorax: anterior lobe pale brown; in dorsal view, medial lobe reddish-brown; hind lobe bluish, nearly straight at the middle, with blunt rounded corners. Pterothorax: black humeral stripe covering upper half of mesepisternum, remainder pale brown.
</paragraph>
