<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis box="[199,305,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[322,403,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,198,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[155,1433,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus: a—dorsal view of a lectotype of Leptagrion andromache Hagen in Selys, 1876 and paratype´s labels (IRSNB); b—lateral view of L. andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; c—lateral view of holotype of Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (FAAL); d—Comparison between Leptagrion andromache and Leptagrion jeromei forewing pterostigma." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704350/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
). S1–2 dorsally dark brown, remainder pale brown; S3–5 light brown dorsally, pale brown laterally, S6–9 dark brown dorsally, pale greenish-brown laterally with black basal rings; anterior portion of S10 black dorsolaterally, remainder brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis box="[199,395,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Anal appendages</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[413,537,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1377,1401]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,192,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[154,1433,181,1353]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male Appendages: a—lateral view of a lectotype of Leptagrion andromache Hagen in Selys, 1876 (IRSNB); b—dorsal view (same specimen of a); c—lateral view of a paratype of Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (FAAL); d—dorsal view (same specimen of c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704354" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704354/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Figs. 3c–d</figureCitation>
). Dark brown; subequal in length to S10; in lateral view, with a small, dorsal, blunt, medial projection; in dorsal view, distal tooth short, not reaching middle portion of cercus, with blunt tips directed anteromedially.
</paragraph>
